items.title: Elon Musk is trying to 'influence' elections, Germany spokesperson says
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:

items.title: South Koreans criticize government for its handling of plane crash
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Bereaved family members of the victims of a fatal plane fire on Monday criticized the South Korean government for their failure to preserve the victims' bodies. Park Han Shin, a representative of the bereaved families, said that the government has not kept their promise to preserve the bodies in freezer containers, saying they are not protecting their dignity. (AP Video/Johnson Lai). Read more: https://bit.ly/4fD9eMj

items.title: Trump wants voting changes. Republicans in Congress will try to make that happen
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Republicans in Congress plan to move quickly in 2025 in their effort to overhaul the nation’s voting procedures. They want to push through long-sought changes such as voter ID and proof-of-citizenship requirements. (AP Video: Sharon Johnson, Serkan Gurbuz). Read more: https://bit.ly/4gBmJgV

items.title: LIVE: Outside The Carter Center after Jimmy Carter dies at 100
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
AP is live from outside The Carter Center in Atlanta after the 39th U.S. President Jimmy Carter died on Sunday, more than a year after entering hospice care, at his home in the small town of Plains, Georgia, where he and his wife, Rosalynn, who died at 96 in November 2023, spent most of their lives, The Carter Center said.

#jimmycarter #live #news

items.title: U.N. aid agencies bring supplies to Indonesian hospital in Gaza Strip
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Agencies delivered supplies to the Indonesia hospital in northern Gaza, as well as continuing an evacuation operation to get patients to Gaza City. The medical facility just outside of the territory’s largest refugee camp in Jabaliya has been under Israeli bombardment for weeks.

items.title: LIVE: Site of plane crash in South Korea that killed 179
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Live from Muan airport in South Korea where a Jeju Air passenger plane skidded off a runway, slammed into a concrete fence and burst into flames on Sunday after its landing gear apparently failed to deploy, killing all but two of the 181 people aboard. Read more here: https://bit.ly/4fDVVew

items.title: South Korea struggles to determine cause of plane crash that killed 179
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
The Boeing 737-800 operated by Jeju Air plane arrived from Bangkok and crashed while attempting to land in the town of Muan, about 290 kilometers (180 miles) south of Seoul. It's come at a time of political upheaval for South Korea, with its government in turmoil. The AP's Rafael Wober explains. Read more: https://bit.ly/4fDVVew

items.title: Booming crow population damages Kenya's economy and ecosystems
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Crows in Kenya have become such a pest that there are fears they will hurt the economy and disrupt local eco systems. Some people are turning to poison to cull the birds. (AP video shot by: Desmond Tiro).
